==English==

===Etymology===
Old English [[halig]], compare German [[heilige]]

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈhoʊli/}}, {{SAMPA|/"hoUli/}}
* {{audio|en-us-holy.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|əʊli}}
* Homophones: [[holey]], [[wholly]] (depends on accent or dialect)

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|holier|holiest}}

# Dedicated to a [[religious]] purpose or a [[god]].
# To be [[revered]] according to a [[religion]].
# To be [[perfect]] or [[flawless]].
# Separated or set apart from something unto something or someone else.
# Set apart or dedicated for a specific purpose, or for use by a single entity or person.
# {{slang}}: An intensifier in an interjection.
#: '''''Holy''' cow, I can’t believe he actually lost the race!''

